It follows violent clashes in the city between his supporters and those of opposition UFDG candidate Cellou Dalein Diallo, who had planned to visit the area. Kankan is a ruling party stronghold but the wider region is also home to many Fulani people, the same community Diallo hails from, reports BBC Afrique's Lalla Sy. Our reporter says the latest violence appears to be a reprisal for an attack by angry youths on the motorcade of Guinea's Prime Minister, Kassory Fofana, who had campaigned in the UFDG stronghold of Lab√© a fortnight ago. Some 30 people were injured in that attack and damage to property was reported. --BBC--